    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-16T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="414"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.113/10465: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Damm</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-16T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 16, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For American Consul at Guaymas.</p>
                <p>Your March 13, 5 p.m.<note n="20" xml:id="d414fn20">See telegram of March 14,
                        noon, from the Consul at Nogales, <ref target="#pg_363">p. 363</ref>.</note>
                    Department has no objection to exportation of fuel oil to Mexico in accordance
                    with plan outlined by you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
